OL,3,CPolice force destroys records relating
OL,4,Cto Miners' Strike and Orgreave
OL,6,FA Northumbria Police spokesperson
OL,7,Fsaid: "We can confirm two boxes
OL,8,Fcontaining data in relation to the
OL,9,FMiners' Strike were disposed of in
OL,10,FApril 2024 following a formal review,
OL,11,Fretain or disposal process in line
OL,12,Fwith force policy and the Data
OL,13,FProtection Act 2018."
OL,15,F'Absolutely alarming'
OL,17,FLabour committed to hold an inquiry or
OL,18,Finvestigation into Orgreave in their
OL,19,Fmanifesto ahead of the 2024 election.
OL,26,@oD@GOU
